# AI Workbench — web UI sample environment file.
#
# Copy to `apps/web/.env` and edit if your local runtime is not on
# `:8080`. `.env` is gitignored; this template is committed.
#
# Vite reads this at `npm run dev:web` startup. None of these values
# are baked into the production bundle — the shipped Docker image
# serves the UI same-origin with the runtime, so no proxy is needed.

# Where the dev server proxies `/api/*`, `/auth/*`, and `/docs` to.
# Defaults to `http://localhost:8080`, which matches `npm run dev`
# in the repo root.
#
# VITE_API_TARGET=http://localhost:8080
